sentences.sentence: The economy of the province was atypical because it was particularly small.
sentences.translation: 该省的经济并不算典型，因为它的规模特别小。

sentences.sentence: Blood routine test showed eosinophilia in 6 cases, atypical lymphocytes in 2 cases and monocytosis in 3 cases.
sentences.translation: 血液常规检查显示嗜酸性粒细胞增多6例，非典型淋巴细胞2例，单核细胞增多3例。

sentences.sentence: The case of penicilliposis marneffei was misdiagnosed as atypical tuberculous arthritis, dermatomyositis or polyarteritis nodosa.
sentences.translation: 马尔尼菲青霉菌病被误诊为非典型结核性关节炎，皮肌炎或者结节性多发性动脉炎。
